name: sir_model
full text: The susceptible-infected-recovered (SIR) model in a closed population was proposed by Kermack and McKendrick as a special case of a more general model and forms the framework of many compartmental models.

name: susceptible
full text: Susceptible individuals S are infected by infected individuals I at a per-capita rate βI and infected individuals recover at a per-capita rate γ to become recovered individuals R.
